        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 21 at 2:30PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 230 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fayette, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eldridge, Cody, Stone Wall, Bazemore, Bankston, Richard Arthur Field,
Berry, Kansas, West Corona, Fayette County Public Lake, Fayette,
Bevill State College Fayette, Hubbertville, Fowlers Crossroads,
Corona, Crossville, Belk, Kennedy, Carbon Hill, and Glen Allen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
